videos.description: T.J. Smith stunts to the left behind his teammates to sack LSU quarterback Danny Etling and force a punt.
videos.headline: Razorbacks stunt to sack Etling

videos.description: On third down, Tigers' quarterback Danny Etling fits a pass in tight window to Dee Anderson for the first down.
videos.headline: Etling rifles pass for LSU first down

videos.description: LSU's Danny Etling launches a 45-yard pass downfield to D.J. Chark who beats a Razorback defender for the game's first score.
videos.headline: Chark gets behind Arkansas secondary for TD

videos.description: Arkansas' Devwah Whaley takes the hand-off and plunges into the end zone to tie LSU at 7-7 just before halftime.
videos.headline: Razorbacks' up-tempo offense punches ball in

videos.description: LSU's head coach Ed Orgeron says that the Razorbacks did a good job stopping the Tigers' rushing attack in the first half, but hopes to spread out the Arkansas defense to find holes in the second half.
videos.headline: Orgeron hopes run game opens up in second half

videos.description: Derrius Guice runs like a battering ram through the Arkansas defense for the 6-yard score to take a 13-7 lead.
videos.headline: Guice gets going in second half for LSU

videos.description: Arkansas' Austin Allen uses a play-action-fake to set up a screen to Will Gragg for 33 yards to set up a Razorbacks field goal.
videos.headline: Razorbacks move down field with TE screen

videos.description: LSU's Derrius Guice finds a hole and outruns the Arkansas defense for his second score of the second half.
videos.headline: Guice slashes Razorbacks defense for 33-yard score

videos.description: LSU's D.J. Chark shows why he is nicknamed "Flash" with a 68-yard catch and run for his second score of the day as LSU jumps to a 26-10 lead over Arkansas.
videos.headline: Chark burns Arkansas for 68-yard TD

videos.description: LSU's Derrius Guice's third score comes on a powerful one-yard run through the Razorbacks defensive line to put the Tigers up 33-10.
videos.headline: Guice taking over game with third score

videos.description: LSU head coach Ed Orgeron explains his pride in LSU's win over Arkansas and the decisions QB Danny Etling made in the second half.
videos.headline: Orgeron: 'It means a lot' to win his second Golden Boot

videos.description: Derrius Guice runs for 147 yards and three touchdowns in LSU's 33-10 victory over Arkansas.
videos.headline: LSU snaps Arkansas's two-game winning streak
